-- int_deduped_channels.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate customer channels to keep the latest attribution per customer
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_revenue_by_channel.sql
```sql
-- Aggregate revenue and transaction metrics by channel and city
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        t.transaction_id,
        t.customer_id,
        t.amount,
        COALESCE(cc.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel,
        COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_channels') }} cc
        ON t.customer_id = cc.customer_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_stores') }} s
        ON t.store_id = s.store_id
)
SELECT
    channel,
    city,
    SUM(amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM source
GROUP BY
    channel,
    city
